The Indigenous women-led initiative in Sumatra promotes safe forest conservation for Indigenous women, and its heritage is intertwined with the forest. 

Our harmony with all our relatives includes the forest, water, animals, humans, sun, moon, and soil. The vision of this community is an indigenized, inclusive world valuing Indigenous knowledge, ways of being, and guardianship in conservation and climate efforts. 

We are looking for people interested in a small-group photography and storytelling workshop designed for those interested in understanding and documenting the dynamics of global consumption and wildlife conservation within the context of social change. 

Captivating images made during our Storytelling School Indonesia 2023. 

Participants will gain firsthand experience in creating visually powerful, truthful, and impactful stories and narratives. 

Join us this september. 🍃 

All the information is in our profile link 

📸 @anncoolsphotography

Cannes Film Festival: You need to fire this woman! 

I completely understand the protocols of the red carpet. A lot of celebrities, you want to get them inside the theater, I get it. 

But that does not justify the actions of this woman. To put her hands on a guest that is attending the festival SHOULD NEVER HAPPEN. To put your hands on anyone should never happen. 

In this clip she is using force to make the Dominican actress, Massiel Taveras  go inside of the theater. Massiel Taveras is also not the first person that the same woman did this too. Kelly Rowland and Lim Yoona received the same treatment. 

Cannes Film Festival, people that you hire are the representation of your and your organization and situations like this should never happen.
